'''''Ficus dammaropsis''''', Kapiak (), or Highland Breadfruit (), is tropical  with huge pleated leaves 60cm across. It is native to the highlands and highlands fringe of . It generally grows at altitudes of between 800 and 2750 s; its extreme range is from sea level to 2820m. Its fruit is edible but rarely eaten except as an emergency food (Bourke nd:4, 11). The young leaves are pickled or cooked and eaten as a vegetable with pig meat (Kambuou 1996:22).
, New Zealand]]With its bold tropical leaves and relative tolerance of cold, ''F. dammaropsis'' is in demand as an ornamental tree in frost-free climates.